00:00:57.870 --> 00:01:02.430
And it was answered last
week in a Facebook post

00:01:02.430 --> 00:01:04.410
about quantum consciousness.

00:01:04.410 --> 00:01:07.080
So I got all four of
them from him at once.

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:10.140
It is a simple question, much
simpler than any of the things

00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:11.220
that you deal with.

00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:13.950
And yet, it is a fairly
unfamiliar question.

00:01:13.950 --> 00:01:16.404
People do tend to
balk at this question.

00:01:16.404 --> 00:01:17.820
So the way I'm
going to do this is

00:01:17.820 --> 00:01:21.630
I'm going to frame the question
and then pause for challenges,

00:01:21.630 --> 00:01:23.700
kick the tires on
this thing, really

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:26.280
try to get clear on the
question, challenges,

00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:28.890
questions, all of that, and
then give you a new proposed

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:33.030
answer, which is unlike anything
I've seen from other sources.

00:01:33.030 --> 00:01:37.010
The question is, what
are striving selves?

00:01:37.010 --> 00:01:38.450
I strive, therefore I am.

00:01:38.450 --> 00:01:40.130
You know, Descartes said,
I think, therefore I am.

00:01:40.130 --> 00:01:41.713
I'm going to go much
deeper than that.

00:01:41.713 --> 00:01:42.260
I strive.

00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:43.010
I try.

00:01:43.010 --> 00:01:44.360
I make effort.

00:01:44.360 --> 00:01:45.560
This doesn't make effort.

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:47.180
Computers don't
actually make effort.

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:48.260
They do work.

00:01:48.260 --> 00:01:50.540
They do very useful work,
but they don't make effort.

00:01:50.540 --> 00:01:52.100
They are not striving.

00:01:52.100 --> 00:01:55.370
And I'll be more specific
about that in a minute.

00:01:55.370 --> 00:01:59.240
You can call us any number of
things, and agent organism,

00:01:59.240 --> 00:01:59.925
living being.

00:01:59.925 --> 00:02:01.790
And I'm just going
to call us selves.

00:02:01.790 --> 00:02:05.030
And I'm going to call us
all selves, that every one

00:02:05.030 --> 00:02:06.940
of these organisms is striving.

00:02:06.940 --> 00:02:11.180
It is doing work
for its own benefit.

00:02:11.180 --> 00:02:13.525
"Striving" means not
going with the flow.

00:02:13.525 --> 00:02:20.030
And you can see that here in
this self, going upstream.

00:02:20.030 --> 00:02:23.580
And it's more than this.

00:02:23.580 --> 00:02:26.840
It's more than just going
upstream because, really,

00:02:26.840 --> 00:02:29.060
what's going on is we are
going against the flow

00:02:29.060 --> 00:02:31.340
towards the
degeneration, everything

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:34.460
falling towards entropy,
randomness, disorder,

00:02:34.460 --> 00:02:36.890
falling apart and petering out.

00:02:36.890 --> 00:02:39.650
So a very simple,
straightforward question.

00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:41.470
We don't.

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:43.990
We run to stay in place
like the Red Queen

00:02:43.990 --> 00:02:45.790
in "Alice Through
the Looking Glass."

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:48.820
And it's happening right now,
unconsciously and unfelt,

00:02:48.820 --> 00:02:52.030
striving, like what our
bodies are doing right now.

00:02:52.030 --> 00:02:55.030
Right now, my body is
regenerating itself faster

00:02:55.030 --> 00:02:55.930
than it degenerates.

00:02:55.930 --> 00:02:58.150
And it's doing it
without me understanding

00:02:58.150 --> 00:03:00.520
what it's doing, without
any awareness of it,

00:03:00.520 --> 00:03:02.740
just like it does in bacteria.

00:03:02.740 --> 00:03:04.540
That is, they don't
have consciousness.

00:03:04.540 --> 00:03:06.280
They don't have feelings.

00:03:06.280 --> 00:03:08.620
And yet, they are striving
against the tendency

00:03:08.620 --> 00:03:11.332
to degenerate.

00:03:11.332 --> 00:03:13.790
So really, we can distinguish
between two kinds of things--

00:03:13.790 --> 00:03:16.610
the things that exist, lasting
as they degenerate, depending

00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:19.640
on their durability, and
selves, which persist,

00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:21.620
striving to regenerate.

00:03:21.620 --> 00:03:25.820
Very big difference, as yet
unexplained by the sciences.

00:03:25.820 --> 00:03:27.560
That's the question.

00:03:27.560 --> 00:03:30.640
And as I said, machines
are not striving selves.

00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:33.220
We engineer them for durability.

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:35.560
Computers aren't striving
selves, and striving selves

00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:36.880
are not computers.

00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:38.680
I adore computers.

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:40.060
I live on them.

00:03:40.060 --> 00:03:41.680
I spend most of my time on them.

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.300
This is not a Luddite talking.

00:03:43.300 --> 00:03:46.360
I'm not protesting against
the use of computers

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:47.890
as though they are heartless.

00:03:47.890 --> 00:03:50.780
No, I think they're full of
heart, the way I use them.

00:03:50.780 --> 00:03:53.770
But they are not striving.

00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:55.840
So the question
comes down to this.

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:57.250
There's no magic added.

00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:59.620
And yet, selves are
means-to-ends striving,

00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:01.810
not just cause-and-effect
mechanism.

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:03.580
There's something
different about us

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:06.010
from nothing but chemistry.

00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:08.260
So I rule out from
the start the idea

00:04:08.260 --> 00:04:10.890
that there's some magic
non-thing thingie that gets

00:04:10.890 --> 00:04:13.390
deposited into matter
that makes us come alive--

00:04:13.390 --> 00:04:16.060
a soul, a spirit, a vital
force, or any of that.

00:04:16.060 --> 00:04:18.579
None of that will work,
nor will the argument

00:04:18.579 --> 00:04:21.632
that there's something about
all interactions, all material

00:04:21.632 --> 00:04:23.090
interactions, all
cause and effect,

00:04:23.090 --> 00:04:25.215
that's actually a little
bit means-to-ends, and you

00:04:25.215 --> 00:04:28.050
collect enough of that together,
and suddenly, poof, it's

00:04:28.050 --> 00:04:29.740
a suddenly striving self.

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:32.080
No, I'm ruling all of that out.

00:04:32.080 --> 00:04:34.360
And also, I'm ruling out
the argument that all we are

00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:37.465
is cause-and-effect mechanism,
which really does corner us

00:04:37.465 --> 00:04:39.100
with a challenge.

00:04:39.100 --> 00:04:41.070
What are striving selves?

00:04:41.070 --> 00:04:46.150
There's a fundamental gap in our
research, scientific research.

00:04:46.150 --> 00:04:49.300
Striving selves are inadmissible
in the physical sciences.

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:51.310
If you had a physics
professor who told you

00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:54.550
that the moon strives to pull
on the tides for someone's

00:04:54.550 --> 00:04:57.640
benefit, you'd think
there's something wrong.

00:04:57.640 --> 00:05:00.070
But down the hall,
you've got a biologist,

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:03.250
or a social scientist,
who can talk all they

00:05:03.250 --> 00:05:04.990
want about striving selves.

00:05:04.990 --> 00:05:08.920
So there's this
fundamental rift.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:11.110
Take these three terms,
absolutely essential

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:11.710
in biology.

00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:16.060
You cannot do biology without
functional, basically function,

00:05:16.060 --> 00:05:18.400
fittedness, and striving.

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:19.900
That's about selves.

00:05:19.900 --> 00:05:21.520
That's about selves
engaging in what

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:24.280
I'll call self-directed
work, effort by selves,

00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:28.450
for themselves, responsive
to their circumstances.

00:05:28.450 --> 00:05:30.680
And the way it works for
continuity in the sciences

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.750
is that the lower
level scientists

00:05:32.750 --> 00:05:36.250
have to explain what the
higher sciences assume.

00:05:36.250 --> 00:05:38.190
And we've got a huge gap here.

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.970
Because chemistry does
not explain functional

00:05:40.970 --> 00:05:42.380
fitted striving.

00:05:42.380 --> 00:05:44.390
And yet, we totally
rely on it in the life

00:05:44.390 --> 00:05:47.210
and social sciences.

00:05:47.210 --> 00:05:49.230
So the approach I'm
going to promote

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:52.170
is that you start with
striving's patient zero,

00:05:52.170 --> 00:05:55.107
the very first striving self.

00:05:55.107 --> 00:05:56.940
You have to explain how
mattering could ever

00:05:56.940 --> 00:06:01.260
emerge from matter, how you
ever get from chemistry to even

00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:03.030
the most basic striving self.

00:06:03.030 --> 00:06:06.630
And if you do that, you get
to reveal the bare essentials

00:06:06.630 --> 00:06:08.820
without all of the
bells and whistles

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:11.250
that accumulate through
evolutionary history.

00:06:11.250 --> 00:06:12.510
You start simple.

00:06:12.510 --> 00:06:13.890
That is not how
we tend to do it.

00:06:13.890 --> 00:06:15.931
We tend to do it through
cognitive science, which

00:06:15.931 --> 00:06:18.210
starts way too high up.

00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:20.520
It's like trying to explain
hair or from quills,

00:06:20.520 --> 00:06:21.360
porcupine quills.

00:06:21.360 --> 00:06:23.240
They are hair.

00:06:23.240 --> 00:06:30.260
Consciousness is very much
a striving self's property,

00:06:30.260 --> 00:06:32.960
just like quills are like hair.

00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:36.320
But it's very specialized,
and it's highly evolved.

00:06:36.320 --> 00:06:38.660
And it's also a little
bit, cognitive science,

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:43.490
like trying to explain striving
starting with wigs, which

00:06:43.490 --> 00:06:46.550
is an artifact, a
computer as an artifact,

00:06:46.550 --> 00:06:49.340
by which we can try
to determine what it

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:53.304
is about us that is striving.

00:06:53.304 --> 00:06:55.720
You've probably heard of the
hard problem in consciousness

00:06:55.720 --> 00:06:57.340
studies, which is
how do you ever

00:06:57.340 --> 00:06:59.980
get qualia, the
experience, the feeling,

00:06:59.980 --> 00:07:02.320
the sensation of things?

00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.560
But cognitive science works
from a computational model

00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:07.030
for what living is.

00:07:07.030 --> 00:07:08.862
So I consider it the
made harder problem.

00:07:08.862 --> 00:07:11.320
If you're going to try to go
from computation, which is not

00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:13.921
striving to do anything,
and go straight to qualia,

00:07:13.921 --> 00:07:15.170
you're going to have problems.

00:07:15.170 --> 00:07:18.490
That's why I suggest we start
with patient zero, that is,

00:07:18.490 --> 00:07:22.930
with the very first
possible striving self.

00:07:22.930 --> 00:07:25.870
And I'll say this is a question
behind our biggest questions.

00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:29.320
To reckon with consciousness,
mind, qualia, free will,

00:07:29.320 --> 00:07:33.460
morality, mortality,
spirituality, astrobiology,

00:07:33.460 --> 00:07:36.550
et cetera, start by explaining
how the first striving self

00:07:36.550 --> 00:07:39.660
could emerge from chemistry.

00:07:39.660 --> 00:07:42.060
So here is the mystery laid out.

00:07:42.060 --> 00:07:43.230
We've got names.

00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:47.580
We've got names for what selves
are, for their properties,

00:07:47.580 --> 00:07:48.450
for their behaviors.

00:07:48.450 --> 00:07:51.060
We've got nouns and
adjectives and verbs.

00:07:51.060 --> 00:07:55.060
And they all remain as yet
unexplained by these terms

00:07:55.060 --> 00:07:56.970
from the physical sciences.

00:07:56.970 --> 00:08:00.750
So you can call us organisms,
subjects, agents, individuals,

00:08:00.750 --> 00:08:02.550
living beings, creatures.

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:04.440
You can even call
us spirits or souls.

00:08:04.440 --> 00:08:07.470
It doesn't actually
matter what we call them.

00:08:07.470 --> 00:08:11.400
These are names that flag
what has yet to be explained.

00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:14.640
They just are markers
that we use to say,

00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:17.524
this is something we
have yet to explain.

00:08:17.524 --> 00:08:19.440
And you've got all of
these properties and all

00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:22.050
these behaviors
as yet unexplained

00:08:22.050 --> 00:08:23.454
in the physical sciences.

00:08:23.454 --> 00:08:24.870
Saying that you're
a striving self

00:08:24.870 --> 00:08:27.660
is no more scientific
explanation

00:08:27.660 --> 00:08:29.580
than saying you have a soul.

00:08:29.580 --> 00:08:31.350
Both of them are just markers.

00:08:31.350 --> 00:08:34.419
So naming is not explaining.

00:08:34.419 --> 00:08:36.309
Here are some
solutions that we often

00:08:36.309 --> 00:08:40.299
move towards since we have this
gap, and it goes unexplained.

00:08:40.299 --> 00:08:43.400
And I'm going to suggest
that they don't work.

00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:45.470
Natural selection--
there's an idea out there

00:08:45.470 --> 00:08:50.250
that the universe was rolling
along with its natural laws,

00:08:50.250 --> 00:08:52.080
and then, suddenly,
a new one enters

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:54.060
called natural selection,
and suddenly, it

00:08:54.060 --> 00:08:55.979
gives rise to organisms.

00:08:55.979 --> 00:08:56.520
Doesn't work.

00:08:56.520 --> 00:08:59.300
Natural selection is actually
natural degeneration.

00:08:59.300 --> 00:09:02.050
It's selves failing
to self-regenerate.

00:09:02.050 --> 00:09:06.050
It explains the honing,
not what's honed.

00:09:06.050 --> 00:09:08.370
To say that natural
selection explains life

00:09:08.370 --> 00:09:12.080
is like saying that
erosion explains mountains.

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:14.330
Yeah, it explains
how they're sculpted,

00:09:14.330 --> 00:09:16.390
but not what they are.

00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:18.720
So I want to say natural
selection doesn't start life.

00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:21.030
Life starts natural selection.

00:09:21.030 --> 00:09:23.880
You actually have to have
striving selves before you have

00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:27.270
evolution as we think of it.

00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:29.160
Another idea is
molecular replication,

00:09:29.160 --> 00:09:31.650
in particular, RNA molecules,
because they are so

00:09:31.650 --> 00:09:33.510
important to us organisms now.

00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:36.360
But the idea is that you would
get molecular replication.

00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:38.160
What you've got
here are examples

00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:41.070
of molecules not being created
from scratch as conservation

00:09:41.070 --> 00:09:41.570
of matter.

00:09:41.570 --> 00:09:43.720
It's transforming of molecules.

00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:47.130
So you get these molecules
going through their chemical

00:09:47.130 --> 00:09:48.240
reactions.

00:09:48.240 --> 00:09:50.280
But the chemical
reactions can appear

00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:53.630
to strive, but then
so can anything.

00:09:53.630 --> 00:09:56.720
A river can look like it's
striving to get to the sea.

00:09:56.720 --> 00:09:58.730
And actually, chemical
reactions like that

00:09:58.730 --> 00:10:00.170
are just going with the flow.

00:10:00.170 --> 00:10:02.390
So this idea that molecular
replication somehow

00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:05.150
solves the problem will not do.

00:10:05.150 --> 00:10:07.820
And energy gradients
degenerate first.

00:10:07.820 --> 00:10:08.720
They peter out.

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:12.480
You saw that in these two
examples I just gave you.

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:14.280
But the material
order can remain,

00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:15.480
degenerating more slowly.

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:18.130
It's still not striving selves.

00:10:21.080 --> 00:10:23.580
How about genes?

00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:25.830
Genes sometimes is used for
the molecules themselves,

00:10:25.830 --> 00:10:27.456
as if a DNA molecule is a gene.

00:10:27.456 --> 00:10:28.830
But mostly, what
we mean by it is

00:10:28.830 --> 00:10:30.930
the sequences within the genes.

00:10:30.930 --> 00:10:33.210
Sequences are not
striving selves,

00:10:33.210 --> 00:10:35.490
but interpreted by them.

00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:38.350
DNA, if you lay it on
a table, is lifeless,

00:10:38.350 --> 00:10:40.620
so to argue that it's
the secret of life

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:42.210
seems to be missing something.

00:10:42.210 --> 00:10:44.520
It's not this magical
molecule that's sometimes

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:46.479
depicted as the secret to life.

00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:49.020
It's a little like saying the
text, which is also a sequence,

00:10:49.020 --> 00:10:51.075
is striving to
tell you something.

00:10:51.075 --> 00:10:53.700
Another striving self is telling
you something with their text,

00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:55.530
but the text itself
is not actually

00:10:55.530 --> 00:10:56.865
striving to tell you anything.

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:02.500
Or the alternative, which is
that it's just cause-and-effect

00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:06.710
relationships, as if the
sequence, the genetic code,

00:11:06.710 --> 00:11:08.570
which yields a one-to-one
correspondence--

00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:11.530
a code is a material
cause-and-effect process--

00:11:11.530 --> 00:11:14.310
is somehow all there is, which
is another popular notion

00:11:14.310 --> 00:11:15.980
about it.

00:11:15.980 --> 00:11:17.370
I want to be clear on this.

00:11:17.370 --> 00:11:19.080
One of the places
where we get messed up

00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:21.690
on this, and in the sciences,
and also in philosophy,

00:11:21.690 --> 00:11:24.480
is to treat it all as causality.

00:11:24.480 --> 00:11:26.910
Interpretation is not causality.

00:11:26.910 --> 00:11:30.360
A stop sign doesn't cause you to
stop unless you crash into it.

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:34.500
We stop because we interpret
it, given our strivings, as

00:11:34.500 --> 00:11:37.170
about traffic, for our benefit.

00:11:37.170 --> 00:11:40.290
So interpretation is
radically different from cause

00:11:40.290 --> 00:11:42.170
and effect.

00:11:42.170 --> 00:11:45.290
Complexity, the reason I have
a frog on the cover of my book

00:11:45.290 --> 00:11:47.720
is that in the book, I
pose the question, which

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:51.292
is more complex, a frog
or a frog smoothie.

00:11:51.292 --> 00:11:54.820
Now, technically, a frog
smoothie is more complex.

00:11:54.820 --> 00:11:57.610
There's poor correlation, and
there's almost no correlation

00:11:57.610 --> 00:12:00.190
between the molecules,
once they're all shaken up,

00:12:00.190 --> 00:12:02.500
once they've degenerated
with a blender.

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:06.190
But also, they would
degenerate anyway.

00:12:06.190 --> 00:12:08.290
That's actually more
complex than the frog.

00:12:08.290 --> 00:12:10.180
The frog has more regularities.

00:12:10.180 --> 00:12:11.860
It would be easier
to describe, which

00:12:11.860 --> 00:12:14.320
is the metric for complexity.

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:17.410
So we often get
ambiguous with this.

00:12:17.410 --> 00:12:19.450
Is it more complex or
just harder to explain?

00:12:19.450 --> 00:12:22.180
The frog is harder to explain,
and yet, less complex.

00:12:22.180 --> 00:12:23.980
It's regularizations.

00:12:23.980 --> 00:12:26.860
It's the orderliness
within a frog

00:12:26.860 --> 00:12:30.600
that is so impressive
and so hard to explain.

00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:32.080
How about AI?

00:12:32.080 --> 00:12:33.850
Not striving, but
engineer-trained

00:12:33.850 --> 00:12:35.410
to aid our striving.

00:12:35.410 --> 00:12:38.380
If you connected a
jillion AI supercomputers

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:40.220
on a sterile planet,
what do you get?

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:41.570
You get a sterile planet.

00:12:41.570 --> 00:12:44.830
That is, no quantity
of AI by itself

00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:49.330
is going to yield
you striving selves.

00:12:49.330 --> 00:12:52.600
Quantum mechanics, quantum
phenomena doesn't strive.

00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:57.490
Striving selves persist at the
classical, non-quantum level.

00:12:57.490 --> 00:12:59.470
Like jilted lovers,
many researchers

00:12:59.470 --> 00:13:02.310
would rather not discuss it.

00:13:02.310 --> 00:13:04.190
They dance around the
gap by equivocation,

00:13:04.190 --> 00:13:06.980
basically talking out both
sides of their mouths.

00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:10.220
I read these glorious
books by your neighbor,

00:13:10.220 --> 00:13:11.690
for example, Robert
Sapolsky, who

00:13:11.690 --> 00:13:13.398
wrote this wonderful
book called "Behave"

00:13:13.398 --> 00:13:17.500
all about the biochemistry
of motivation.

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:19.070
I love these books.

00:13:19.070 --> 00:13:21.320
And yet, they are still
dodging the question.

00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:25.290
He'll talk about how a
molecule causes a motivation.

00:13:25.290 --> 00:13:27.060
It's not clear how that happens.

00:13:27.060 --> 00:13:29.970
And he doesn't seem
to be addressing it.

00:13:29.970 --> 00:13:33.770
You get a book like
"Information," a theory--

00:13:33.770 --> 00:13:36.090
what is it, "A History,
a Theory, a Flood,"

00:13:36.090 --> 00:13:37.530
by James Gleick.

00:13:37.530 --> 00:13:39.570
Wonderful book, which,
by the end of it,

00:13:39.570 --> 00:13:42.180
claims that there's
information everywhere

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:45.337
and has always been, by the
end of the middle section.

00:13:45.337 --> 00:13:46.920
And then he goes
into the last section

00:13:46.920 --> 00:13:50.850
about how we're now experiencing
a flood of information.

00:13:50.850 --> 00:13:51.630
Which is it?

00:13:51.630 --> 00:13:53.640
Is it always everywhere?

00:13:53.640 --> 00:13:55.921
Or is it something we can
experience a flood of?

00:13:55.921 --> 00:13:57.420
If we experience a
flood of it, then

00:13:57.420 --> 00:14:01.050
apparently we are interpreting
it in a different way

00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:02.306
than we used to.

00:14:02.306 --> 00:14:03.930
But the claim that
it's all information

00:14:03.930 --> 00:14:06.910
is a kind of equivocation.

00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:10.200
So information can be
talked about so it's just

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:11.940
Shannon reductions
and possibilities,

00:14:11.940 --> 00:14:15.540
or as a difference that makes
a difference for a self that

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:20.760
is striving to stay
alive, to regenerate.

00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:23.342
So that's the question.

00:14:23.342 --> 00:14:25.050
And I want to hear
your challenges to it.

00:14:25.050 --> 00:14:27.900
I want to hear you really
kick the tires on this,

00:14:27.900 --> 00:14:30.660
really push back if you have
trouble with the question,

00:14:30.660 --> 00:14:32.880
or if I haven't been
clear about the question.

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:36.480
And then I'll go on to
a new proposed answer.

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:40.270
No, intentionality would
be a subset of striving.

00:14:40.270 --> 00:14:43.200
The words get really
squirrelly in here.

00:14:43.200 --> 00:14:45.410
That is, they carry
a lot of baggage.

00:14:45.410 --> 00:14:48.450
In my last presentation at
biosemiotics conference,

00:14:48.450 --> 00:14:51.180
I called it trying,
which tends to imply

00:14:51.180 --> 00:14:53.130
a kind of a
psychological intention,

00:14:53.130 --> 00:14:56.650
a will, a conscious effort.

00:14:56.650 --> 00:15:00.160
So I've ended up gravitating
to striving for two reasons.

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:03.330
One, it's fairly clean on this
question of ghost and machine.

00:15:03.330 --> 00:15:05.100
There's a tendency
in this research to--

00:15:05.100 --> 00:15:07.860
I think of it like
walking a tightrope line,

00:15:07.860 --> 00:15:12.660
this question here, because
you can fall off into ghost,

00:15:12.660 --> 00:15:16.140
basically homuncular-- that is,
you're anthropomorphizing what

00:15:16.140 --> 00:15:16.970
goes on--

00:15:16.970 --> 00:15:19.890
or into machine, mechanics,
cause and effect.

00:15:19.890 --> 00:15:22.380
So how you ride that is
difficult with the words

00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:23.130
we've got.

00:15:23.130 --> 00:15:25.380
There are definitions
of intentionality

00:15:25.380 --> 00:15:28.860
that would be broad enough,
that would cover what all living

00:15:28.860 --> 00:15:31.690
beings do, but that's not
the vernacular use of it.

00:15:31.690 --> 00:15:34.710
And we usually think of
it as something willed

00:15:34.710 --> 00:15:37.110
by a conscious, feeling being.

00:15:37.110 --> 00:15:39.400
But yes, it is included in here.

00:15:39.400 --> 00:15:43.110
And by the way, I am not
just striving to regenerate.

00:15:43.110 --> 00:15:45.870
I'm striving, for example,
to communicate an idea.

00:15:45.870 --> 00:15:48.960
That is, by now, humans
have all sorts of headroom

00:15:48.960 --> 00:15:52.200
and all sorts of distractions,
other kinds of intentions.

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:54.540
But if you want to
get at patient zero,

00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:56.040
you start with the
most basic, which

00:15:56.040 --> 00:15:59.530
is pushing against this
tendency to fall apart.

00:15:59.530 --> 00:16:01.710
AUDIENCE: So you mentioned
