You'll notice that I said
that these were something

00:23:12.250 --> 00:23:15.130
like non-parasitic viruses.

00:23:15.130 --> 00:23:18.130
But there's no DNA
in these things.

00:23:18.130 --> 00:23:21.430
The reading of sequences in
the service of your striving

00:23:21.430 --> 00:23:23.590
is not the kind of thing
you can imagine easily

00:23:23.590 --> 00:23:26.350
coming about spontaneously
out of chemistry.

00:23:26.350 --> 00:23:28.360
It's a very complicated process.

00:23:28.360 --> 00:23:31.030
Terry has a model for
how we could get there.

00:23:31.030 --> 00:23:33.260
But we're starting
simpler than that.

00:23:33.260 --> 00:23:36.450
And as I said, simple,
but not impressionistic.

00:23:36.450 --> 00:23:39.930
OK, now let me back up and
tell you how I got there,

00:23:39.930 --> 00:23:43.430
how we get there, to your
to-don'ts, basically,

00:23:43.430 --> 00:23:45.020
your experience of life.

00:23:45.020 --> 00:23:46.910
You focus rather than dithering.

00:23:46.910 --> 00:23:48.830
You could have done
dozens of other things

00:23:48.830 --> 00:23:50.610
right now during your hour here.

00:23:50.610 --> 00:23:52.520
But you chose to be here.

00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:54.950
And you're not just everywhere.

00:23:54.950 --> 00:23:56.240
You're doing focused work.

00:23:56.240 --> 00:23:58.670
Your focus is a product of
self-control, everything

00:23:58.670 --> 00:24:02.480
you prevent yourself from doing
consciously and unconsciously.

00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:05.270
And above all, you focus on
preventing the degeneration

00:24:05.270 --> 00:24:06.600
of your ability to focus.

00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:09.470
So I'm going to be arguing
that you are a prevention that

00:24:09.470 --> 00:24:10.820
prevents itself from ending.

00:24:13.760 --> 00:24:15.930
It's a process of
elimination logic,

00:24:15.930 --> 00:24:18.030
very different from
the arrow kind of logic

00:24:18.030 --> 00:24:21.090
we use in schematics
and formalizations.

00:24:21.090 --> 00:24:25.062
And it's the insight behind a
lot of very big breakthroughs.

00:24:25.062 --> 00:24:26.520
Pay attention to
what's eliminated.

00:24:26.520 --> 00:24:28.530
Darwin, natural selection--
to explain fitness,

00:24:28.530 --> 00:24:31.450
attend to the
non-survival of the unfit.

00:24:31.450 --> 00:24:34.150
Shannon, signal theory--
to explain signals sent,

00:24:34.150 --> 00:24:36.950
attend to signals not sent.

00:24:36.950 --> 00:24:40.880
Ashby, H. Ross Ashby, who coined
the term "self-organization"--

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:44.920
to explain increased order,
attend to emergent constraint

00:24:44.920 --> 00:24:45.507
on disorder.

00:24:45.507 --> 00:24:47.840
I'm going to have to say more
about emergent constraint.

00:24:47.840 --> 00:24:49.798
Here are two quotes from
him that I like a lot.

00:24:49.798 --> 00:24:52.920
"A self-organizing system
spontaneously reduces

00:24:52.920 --> 00:24:55.460
the number of its
potential states."

00:24:55.460 --> 00:24:59.830
"Observe what might have
happened, but did not."

00:24:59.830 --> 00:25:01.860
Here's an example, an
intuitive example of it,

00:25:01.860 --> 00:25:06.130
threading through a crowd and
others threading around you.

00:25:06.130 --> 00:25:09.000
You'll get these
streams of people

00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:11.880
who are taking the path
of least resistance

00:25:11.880 --> 00:25:15.654
that emerge by a process
of path elimination.

00:25:15.654 --> 00:25:17.820
Now, these are striving
selves, so it doesn't really

00:25:17.820 --> 00:25:20.790
count if we want to
look for patient zero.

00:25:20.790 --> 00:25:24.000
But there are, of course, plenty
of non-living self-organization

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:25.446
processes.

00:25:25.446 --> 00:25:26.820
Now, the term
"self-organization"

00:25:26.820 --> 00:25:27.564
is problematic.

00:25:27.564 --> 00:25:29.730
We were talking a minute
ago about problematic terms

00:25:29.730 --> 00:25:31.230
like "intention."

00:25:31.230 --> 00:25:33.354
It suggests a self
trying to organize it.

00:25:33.354 --> 00:25:34.770
And there are
plenty of people who

00:25:34.770 --> 00:25:38.160
have moved in that direction,
talking as though if you just

00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:41.430
get self-organization going,
and it gets complicated enough,

00:25:41.430 --> 00:25:43.860
then you've got a striving self.

00:25:43.860 --> 00:25:46.410
I actually call it
emergent regularization.

00:25:46.410 --> 00:25:48.450
It's a constraint process.

00:25:48.450 --> 00:25:50.440
And whirlpools are an example.

00:25:50.440 --> 00:25:52.980
Auto-assembly, like
crystal formation,

00:25:52.980 --> 00:25:55.140
and autocatalysis about
which I'll say more now,

00:25:55.140 --> 00:25:58.350
because they're
essential to our model.

00:25:58.350 --> 00:26:01.150
Auto-assembly is basically
crystal formation,

00:26:01.150 --> 00:26:04.180
but all sorts of other processes
as well-- lipid membranes,

00:26:04.180 --> 00:26:07.780
for example, which are
bubbles, or capsids,

00:26:07.780 --> 00:26:08.960
which will be crucial here.

00:26:08.960 --> 00:26:10.360
They're like viral shells.

00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:12.582
They're not actually
constructed deliberately.

00:26:12.582 --> 00:26:14.290
They're not part of
the striving process.

00:26:14.290 --> 00:26:16.900
They actually fall together
just like crystals do.

00:26:16.900 --> 00:26:18.550
They fall to resting states.

00:26:18.550 --> 00:26:21.700
And their resting states, given
their complementary molecular

00:26:21.700 --> 00:26:26.950
geometry, will yield you
regularized sheets, shells,

00:26:26.950 --> 00:26:27.596
and tubes.

00:26:27.596 --> 00:26:28.720
So these are very exciting.

00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:31.360
Remember, we are
trying to figure out

00:26:31.360 --> 00:26:33.460
how to explain the frog.

00:26:33.460 --> 00:26:35.060
Well, the frog is
full of regularity.

00:26:35.060 --> 00:26:37.480
So we might look
to this process,

00:26:37.480 --> 00:26:43.340
auto-assembly, as a step towards
life, towards striving selves.

00:26:43.340 --> 00:26:46.870
Autocatalysis is
basically a chain reaction

00:26:46.870 --> 00:26:51.130
that grows a population
of multiple catalysts

00:26:51.130 --> 00:26:54.580
that are all, in effect,
producing each other.

00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:57.670
It's a population
explosion that grows,

00:26:57.670 --> 00:26:59.890
depletes the resources
that it depends upon,

00:26:59.890 --> 00:27:01.660
and then dissipates.

00:27:01.660 --> 00:27:04.960
So if you imagine you've got
these two molecules, x and y.

00:27:04.960 --> 00:27:07.930
And in this super
simplification of it,

00:27:07.930 --> 00:27:10.360
they are both
transforming reactants--

00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:12.220
I didn't get specific
about the reactants--

00:27:12.220 --> 00:27:13.320
into more of each other.

00:27:13.320 --> 00:27:18.460
An X transforms an R into a
Y. And a Y transforms an R

00:27:18.460 --> 00:27:21.280
into an X. And you get
this population explosion

00:27:21.280 --> 00:27:22.390
of X's and Y's.

00:27:22.390 --> 00:27:24.970
But in the meantime, you're
depleting all the R's.

00:27:24.970 --> 00:27:29.107
And you end up with a
dissipation of the molecules.

00:27:29.107 --> 00:27:30.690
And the thing about
this autocatalysis

00:27:30.690 --> 00:27:35.057
is, it's more likely to start if
you've got a cluster of the X's

00:27:35.057 --> 00:27:35.890
and Y's to start it.

00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:37.810
Yes, it could start
with one X producing

00:27:37.810 --> 00:27:40.720
one Y that then
produces another X.

00:27:40.720 --> 00:27:42.130
But it's way more
likely to start

00:27:42.130 --> 00:27:46.990
if you've got a cluster
of them in close range.

00:27:46.990 --> 00:27:48.820
And often with
byproducts-- for example,

00:27:48.820 --> 00:27:52.600
an X might split an R into
a Y in some other molecule,

00:27:52.600 --> 00:27:56.920
which would also be crucial
to this explanation.

00:27:56.920 --> 00:27:59.420
Self-organization--
so like I said,

00:27:59.420 --> 00:28:01.660
some people think that
self-organization is enough.

00:28:01.660 --> 00:28:03.890
It's a variation on the
complexity argument.

00:28:03.890 --> 00:28:07.290
If you get enough of this kind
of emergent regularization,

00:28:07.290 --> 00:28:10.450
self-organization, suddenly,
it becomes a striving self.

00:28:10.450 --> 00:28:11.650
We don't think so.

00:28:11.650 --> 00:28:14.350
It goes with the flow
towards overall degeneration,

00:28:14.350 --> 00:28:15.160
and selves don't.

00:28:15.160 --> 00:28:17.320
They strive to regenerate.

00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:19.540
But still, this concept
of emergent constraint,

00:28:19.540 --> 00:28:23.070
that is, reduced
possibilities emerging

00:28:23.070 --> 00:28:26.260
throughout a dynamic process,
is of interest to us.

00:28:26.260 --> 00:28:28.000
And we think
there's a way to get

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:32.710
at the origin, the patient zero
of striving selves, through it.

00:28:32.710 --> 00:28:35.140
So just to be clear on
the general principle,

00:28:35.140 --> 00:28:38.650
the whole is less than the sum
of its parts possibilities.

00:28:38.650 --> 00:28:41.410
Any of those people threading
their way through the crowd

00:28:41.410 --> 00:28:43.870
could have moved in a
whole lot more directions,

00:28:43.870 --> 00:28:46.930
but those directions are
reduced through the congestion.

00:28:46.930 --> 00:28:49.820
And they end up taking
paths of least resistance.

00:28:49.820 --> 00:28:51.640
As some probabilities
become less likely,

00:28:51.640 --> 00:28:53.470
others become more likely.

00:28:53.470 --> 00:28:57.040
What's presented is a
product of what's prevented.

00:28:57.040 --> 00:28:58.740
And so we got that
throughout the--

00:28:58.740 --> 00:29:02.614
Darwin, Shannon, Ashby are all
playing with this key insight.

00:29:02.614 --> 00:29:04.530
And basically, what we're
doing is applying it

00:29:04.530 --> 00:29:06.400
to this question, what
is a striving self?

00:29:06.400 --> 00:29:10.240
If it's not your body, if it's
not your DNA and ribosomes,

00:29:10.240 --> 00:29:13.060
what is it?

00:29:13.060 --> 00:29:15.910
So we think of
self-regeneration as possibly

00:29:15.910 --> 00:29:17.890
a higher-level
emergent constraint.

00:29:17.890 --> 00:29:21.310
So we've come up with a testable
hypothesis for how coupled

00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:25.420
self-organizing processes could
prevent each other from ending.

00:29:25.420 --> 00:29:28.660
And like I've said, it has
to be simple and yet not

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:30.010
impressionistic.

00:29:30.010 --> 00:29:32.500
I don't get to say, well,
it looks like it's striving.

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:36.130
It actually has to be doing
work on its own behalf, fit

00:29:36.130 --> 00:29:39.330
to its own environment.

00:29:39.330 --> 00:29:41.640
Requirements for
self-generation, very basic.

00:29:41.640 --> 00:29:43.960
If you think about,
OK, everything's

00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:46.860
degenerating, how would you
keep yourself from degenerating,

00:29:46.860 --> 00:29:48.480
you'd need self-repair,
regenerating

00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:49.950
whatever degenerates.

00:29:49.950 --> 00:29:53.100
You'd need self-protection, that
is, preventing degeneration.

00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:54.540
And you'd need
self-reproduction,

00:29:54.540 --> 00:29:56.248
because, eventually,
you will degenerate,

00:29:56.248 --> 00:30:02.310
and you need lineages of
self-generating striving selves

00:30:02.310 --> 00:30:05.544
that have the capacity to
self-repair and self-protect.

00:30:05.544 --> 00:30:06.960
And out of these
three, you end up

00:30:06.960 --> 00:30:09.360
with this interesting
challenge, what

00:30:09.360 --> 00:30:11.610
I call selective interaction.

00:30:11.610 --> 00:30:13.060
We all deal with it.

00:30:13.060 --> 00:30:15.300
But it had to be there
at the beginning of life.

00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:18.630
That is, in order to do any
of this generative work,

00:30:18.630 --> 00:30:21.106
you need to take in
energy and resources

00:30:21.106 --> 00:30:22.230
and put out waste products.

00:30:22.230 --> 00:30:24.691
And at the same time,
to prevent degeneration,

00:30:24.691 --> 00:30:25.690
you have to not do that.

00:30:25.690 --> 00:30:28.650
So you've got this going on
from the origins of life.

00:30:28.650 --> 00:30:31.230
And that's a challenge for
origins of life research

00:30:31.230 --> 00:30:35.670
because the kinds of selective
membranes that we all rely

00:30:35.670 --> 00:30:38.250
on, that let in some stuff
and not others-- pores,

00:30:38.250 --> 00:30:39.660
and orifices, and all that--

00:30:39.660 --> 00:30:42.360
you're not going to get that
by chance, just a lucky chance

00:30:42.360 --> 00:30:44.000
that lets in all
the right stuff,

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:46.080
lets out all the
right stuff, doesn't

00:30:46.080 --> 00:30:47.850
let in all the
wrong stuff, doesn't

00:30:47.850 --> 00:30:49.620
let in all the wrong stuff.

00:30:49.620 --> 00:30:52.560
That is a
origins-of-life theory.

00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:54.480
And origins of
striving selves has

00:30:54.480 --> 00:30:57.960
to be striving successfully,
outpacing the tendency

00:30:57.960 --> 00:31:02.010
to degenerate from day one, that
it has to be able to do that.

00:31:02.010 --> 00:31:04.609
And this is a challenge,
the selective interaction.

00:31:04.609 --> 00:31:06.400
By the way, you're
still doing all of this.

00:31:06.400 --> 00:31:08.070
Obviously, self-repair,
you're striving

00:31:08.070 --> 00:31:10.500
to keep fit and healthy,
sometimes consciously,

00:31:10.500 --> 00:31:14.040
sometimes not consciously.

00:31:14.040 --> 00:31:16.079
Self-protection, you're
regenerating skin,

00:31:16.079 --> 00:31:17.870
staying clothed with
a roof over your head.

00:31:17.870 --> 00:31:19.514
Self-reproduction, kids maybe.

00:31:19.514 --> 00:31:21.930
And selective interaction,
which has gotten very elaborate

00:31:21.930 --> 00:31:23.050
for human beings.

00:31:23.050 --> 00:31:25.216
There's a little taste of
it in this room right now.

00:31:25.216 --> 00:31:28.980
I'm suggesting something that
you can either absorb or avoid.

00:31:28.980 --> 00:31:30.100
People do all the time.

00:31:30.100 --> 00:31:32.016
We're always trying to
figure out what to take

00:31:32.016 --> 00:31:35.850
and what not to take in at
many levels, from, you can say,

00:31:35.850 --> 00:31:38.820
the immune system to
our mouths all of this.

00:31:38.820 --> 00:31:41.420
All of it's still going on.

00:31:41.420 --> 00:31:45.660
So here, finally, is that model
that I mentioned early on.

00:31:45.660 --> 00:31:48.500
And we got the emulation
of it from Anton.

00:31:48.500 --> 00:31:51.190
Here it is, the autogen,
meaning the self-regenerator.

00:31:53.944 --> 00:31:55.860
Imagine you've got one
of those chain reaction

00:31:55.860 --> 00:31:58.380
processes, the autocatalysis,
but its byproduct

00:31:58.380 --> 00:32:00.750
happens to be one of
those capsid molecules.

00:32:00.750 --> 00:32:03.630
So while it's chain reacting,
in the midst of that chain

00:32:03.630 --> 00:32:05.940
reaction, it's
putting out molecules

00:32:05.940 --> 00:32:08.760
that will form the
equivalent of virus shells.

00:32:08.760 --> 00:32:10.740
Not trying form
them, they just form.

00:32:10.740 --> 00:32:11.730
They fall together.

00:32:11.730 --> 00:32:13.770
That's the auto-assembly.

00:32:13.770 --> 00:32:16.470
So you've got to
complementarity between the two,

00:32:16.470 --> 00:32:19.417
where you get a chain
reaction, and then you've

00:32:19.417 --> 00:32:21.000
got these shells
that encapsulate what

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:24.210
I call starter kits or
seeds, that if they break

00:32:24.210 --> 00:32:26.850
open in the presence
of more reactants

00:32:26.850 --> 00:32:30.540
can resume the autocatalysis,
the chain reaction,

00:32:30.540 --> 00:32:33.030
and resume producing seeds.

00:32:33.030 --> 00:32:34.680
OK, so let's take
a look at this.

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:35.730
You got the reactant.

00:32:35.730 --> 00:32:38.510
You've got a cluster of
these catalysts in here.

00:32:38.510 --> 00:32:41.250
The purple molecules
are the capsids.

00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:42.750
It breaks open.

00:32:42.750 --> 00:32:45.320
Let's say a big
molecule hits it.

00:32:45.320 --> 00:32:48.750
And it's got spill out
into the reactants,

00:32:48.750 --> 00:32:50.830
which generates a
whole lot more seeds,

00:32:50.830 --> 00:32:54.780
X's and Y's, that end up,
by happenstance, captured

00:32:54.780 --> 00:32:56.060
within more of these shells.

00:32:56.060 --> 00:32:58.580
That's the seeds
or starter kits.

00:32:58.580 --> 00:33:01.980
Very simple model.

00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:04.050
Is there self-regeneration?

00:33:04.050 --> 00:33:07.520
Well, it's repairing the
seeds as they degenerate.

00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:11.590
And the capsids protect
against degeneration.

00:33:11.590 --> 00:33:16.180
It generates varied and
evolvable autogen lineages,

00:33:16.180 --> 00:33:18.940
and there's selective
interaction, though not quite.

00:33:18.940 --> 00:33:21.550
It's not actually choosing
when to be open and closed.

00:33:21.550 --> 00:33:23.609
I'll explain how we
get there in a minute.

00:33:23.609 --> 00:33:25.150
But at least you
have an alternation.

00:33:25.150 --> 00:33:27.827
And the alternation
is crucial, given

00:33:27.827 --> 00:33:29.410
that one of the
things that has to fit

00:33:29.410 --> 00:33:32.380
is environments where reactants
are only sometimes present.

00:33:32.380 --> 00:33:35.860
We think of this thing like a
ratchet it grows for a while,

00:33:35.860 --> 00:33:37.510
and then it locks down.

00:33:37.510 --> 00:33:40.360
And while it's locked down,
it can survive in environments

00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:41.680
where there are no reactants.

00:33:41.680 --> 00:33:44.170
That's why it's useful to have
seeds or starter kits that

00:33:44.170 --> 00:33:47.310
are enclosed and basically
static at that point.

00:33:47.310 --> 00:33:49.470
So it's functional in
that it self-repairs

00:33:49.470 --> 00:33:52.230
when broken for its own sake.

00:33:52.230 --> 00:33:54.240
Remember, here's a good
place to not be thinking

00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:55.600
about intentionality.

00:33:55.600 --> 00:33:56.850
It's not trying to.

00:33:56.850 --> 00:33:58.657
It doesn't care.

00:33:58.657 --> 00:33:59.490
It's that conscious.

00:33:59.490 --> 00:34:00.880
It's not willing all of that.

00:34:00.880 --> 00:34:02.562
And yet, we have to
start at that level

00:34:02.562 --> 00:34:04.020
if we're really
going to understand

00:34:04.020 --> 00:34:09.420
that the self-repair benefits
the lineage of autogens.

00:34:09.420 --> 00:34:10.980
It's fitted, as I've mentioned.

00:34:10.980 --> 00:34:11.639
It's striving.

00:34:11.639 --> 00:34:15.210
When seeds are broken, autogens
respond with autocatalytic work

00:34:15.210 --> 00:34:18.440
that regenerate seeds.

00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:20.246
Here's an example of
how it might evolve.

00:34:20.246 --> 00:34:21.620
We argue that, at
this point, you

00:34:21.620 --> 00:34:28.296
have found a way to outpace the
tendency towards degeneration.

00:34:28.296 --> 00:34:30.530
It breaks open.

00:34:30.530 --> 00:34:32.630
Other molecules get into it.

00:34:32.630 --> 00:34:35.449
We have discovered a way
in which it can self-purge.

00:34:35.449 --> 00:34:37.790
That is, it will tend
to get rid of molecules

00:34:37.790 --> 00:34:39.170
that don't facilitate it.

00:34:39.170 --> 00:34:41.840
It breaks open, and
the molecules of copy

00:34:41.840 --> 00:34:44.989
are the X's and Y's, not the
other molecules that are kind

00:34:44.989 --> 00:34:46.440
of strays that enter into it.

00:34:46.440 --> 00:34:49.560
So there's a little bit of
self-purging at this point.

00:34:49.560 --> 00:34:52.760
But imagine that you end
up not with a Y but a Z,

00:34:52.760 --> 00:34:55.330
and the Z happens to have
a different byproduct,

00:34:55.330 --> 00:34:58.010
a different capsid molecule
that's a little rougher

00:34:58.010 --> 00:34:58.910
on the outside.

00:34:58.910 --> 00:35:00.890
And the R's actually
stick to it,

00:35:00.890 --> 00:35:05.710
making the overall seed rougher,
more likely to break open.

00:35:05.710 --> 00:35:08.410
Now, this is the kind
of thing we can emulate.

00:35:08.410 --> 00:35:10.120
I'm not saying
this is the answer.

00:35:10.120 --> 00:35:12.940
But it does show the kinds
of things that could evolve.

00:35:12.940 --> 00:35:15.760
And it is an
attempt to show how,

00:35:15.760 --> 00:35:17.410
from nothing but
physics and chemistry,

00:35:17.410 --> 00:35:19.780
you could actually get a
striving self that would then

00:35:19.780 --> 00:35:22.200
have the capacity to evolve.

00:35:22.200 --> 00:35:25.410
So you can see that
this one actually begins

00:35:25.410 --> 00:35:26.670
to have selective interaction.

00:35:26.670 --> 00:35:30.780
It is more likely to open
in the presence of reactants

00:35:30.780 --> 00:35:34.560
than in the absence
of reactants.

00:35:34.560 --> 00:35:36.020
And then as I
mentioned earlier, we

00:35:36.020 --> 00:35:37.395
have a model for
how you'd end up

00:35:37.395 --> 00:35:40.830
with a template molecule,
a molecule like DNA or RNA

00:35:40.830 --> 00:35:42.450
that has a sequence
that is actually

00:35:42.450 --> 00:35:46.110
functional for
the striving self.

00:35:46.110 --> 00:35:50.220
But we would argue, given
the complexity of making

00:35:50.220 --> 00:35:53.126
use of a sequence,
you really have

00:35:53.126 --> 00:35:54.750
to start with striving
selves if you're

00:35:54.750 --> 00:35:58.110
going to get to the level where
you can actually use DNA and/or

00:35:58.110 --> 00:35:59.680
RNA.

00:35:59.680 --> 00:36:01.440
OK, so what's a striving self?

00:36:01.440 --> 00:36:02.340
It's not a ghost.

00:36:02.340 --> 00:36:03.923
It's not something
added to chemistry.

00:36:03.923 --> 00:36:04.810
It's not mechanism.

00:36:04.810 --> 00:36:07.050
It's not the material energy,
cause-and-effect work,

00:36:07.050 --> 00:36:08.490
or organization.

00:36:08.490 --> 00:36:11.470
It's a self-regenerative
emergent constraint,

00:36:11.470 --> 00:36:15.750
a synergistic coupling between
two self-organization processes

00:36:15.750 --> 00:36:20.220
that prevent each
other's degeneration.

00:36:20.220 --> 00:36:21.240
What is the self then?

00:36:21.240 --> 00:36:23.698
What is a striving self, if
you were to work all the way up

00:36:23.698 --> 00:36:25.140
to all of us?

00:36:25.140 --> 00:36:28.680
I would argue that we are a
constraint that channels energy

00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:33.510
into work that prevents the
constraint's degeneration

00:36:33.510 --> 00:36:38.100
and that it came about
through a synergy between two

00:36:38.100 --> 00:36:41.870
self-organizing processes that
prevent each other from ending.

00:36:41.870 --> 00:36:44.280
Your whole is less than
the sum of your parts'

00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:46.447
independent possibilities.

00:36:46.447 --> 00:36:48.030
So I come back to
emergent constraints

00:36:48.030 --> 00:36:51.060
because I think it may have the
most application in thinking

00:36:51.060 --> 00:36:54.240
here about how to move
AI and other technologies

00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:57.600
beyond where we already
are, to really push it.

00:36:57.600 --> 00:37:00.180
Observe what might have
happened, but did not--

00:37:00.180 --> 00:37:01.740
emergent regularization,
as I said,

00:37:01.740 --> 00:37:04.260
self-organization is
go-with-the-flow, local,

00:37:04.260 --> 00:37:06.840
temporary generation of
energetic and material

00:37:06.840 --> 00:37:07.860
regularities.

00:37:07.860 --> 00:37:09.900
Emergent
self-regeneration, though,

00:37:09.900 --> 00:37:12.240
is selves striving
against the flow

00:37:12.240 --> 00:37:13.829
to prevent their
own degeneration.

00:37:13.829 --> 00:37:15.870
And it happens through
this synergistic coupling,

00:37:15.870 --> 00:37:18.750
where both of them stop
the other from failing.

00:37:18.750 --> 00:37:22.770
Autocatalysis, remember, it
grows and then dissipates,

00:37:22.770 --> 00:37:26.940
while the capsids keep it from
losing all of its potential

00:37:26.940 --> 00:37:28.650
before it dissipates.

00:37:28.650 --> 00:37:31.920
And capsids will break
open and dissipate as well,

00:37:31.920 --> 00:37:34.710
but the autogen
replenishes the supply

00:37:34.710 --> 00:37:37.410
of capsid molecules, these
molecules that form the shells.

00:37:40.600 --> 00:37:43.290
In general, though, there's
a methodological question

00:37:43.290 --> 00:37:46.090
or proposition I want to make.

00:37:46.090 --> 00:37:49.570
Life isn't schematic or formal
like our engineering and math

00:37:49.570 --> 00:37:50.680
simulations.

00:37:50.680 --> 00:37:53.800
It's running gauntlets, selves
constraining possibilities

00:37:53.800 --> 00:37:55.780
to prevent dying.

00:37:55.780 --> 00:37:58.860
It's somehow figuring out how
any organism does anything

00:37:58.860 --> 00:38:01.260
like this, running
through the constraints

00:38:01.260 --> 00:38:03.690
because it is fitted
to the constraints.

00:38:03.690 --> 00:38:09.210
It has, internal to
itself, an agency

00:38:09.210 --> 00:38:14.050
that enables it to avoid all
of the risks of degeneration.

00:38:14.050 --> 00:38:16.890
And in general, I find
that, across the fields--

00:38:16.890 --> 00:38:19.607
in philosophy, in
programming, just

00:38:19.607 --> 00:38:21.690
across the fields-- we're
still using models that,

00:38:21.690 --> 00:38:26.430
in one way or another, apply
point A to point B, kind

00:38:26.430 --> 00:38:28.560
of a Euclidean approach,
that I'm going to say

00:38:28.560 --> 00:38:30.760
is not quite how it works.

00:38:30.760 --> 00:38:33.390
Everything is
random at the start.

00:38:33.390 --> 00:38:35.100
And somehow, life
figures out how

00:38:35.100 --> 00:38:36.700
to narrow in on possibilities.

00:38:36.700 --> 00:38:38.760
It's processes of elimination.

00:38:38.760 --> 00:38:40.770
OK, so just these two takeaways.

00:38:40.770 --> 00:38:43.260
To push the tech envelope,
pay attention to how tech

00:38:43.260 --> 00:38:46.740
simulates but doesn't yet
emulate striving selves.

00:38:46.740 --> 00:38:49.230
And that's the thing
we can talk about.

00:38:49.230 --> 00:38:51.630
And the other is to
emulate, pay attention

00:38:51.630 --> 00:38:54.390
to emergent constraints,
not schematic arrowing,

00:38:54.390 --> 00:38:57.000
but dynamic narrowing
of possibilities.

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:58.920
Thank you.

